Kathryn B. COHEN, Appellant, v. James E. (Bill) DECKER et al., Appellees. No. 12416. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit Nov. 17, 1948. H. C. Shropshire, of Weatherford, Tex., for appellant. H. P. Kucera, City Atty., of Dallas, Tex., Milton Unger, of New York City, W. C. Gowan and Emil Corenbleth, both of Dallas, Tex., J. Kirkman Jackson, of Birmingham, Ala., Will R. Wilson, Jr., Dist. Atty., Douglas E. Bergman, 1st Asst. Dist Atty. and E. B. Stroud, all of Dallas, Tex., Archie C. Price, of Grand Prairie, Tex., and D. A. Frank and D. A. Frank, Jr., both of Dallas, Tex., for appellees.

Before HOLMES, WALLER, and LEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment appealed from is affirmed.
